The Cape Town bus service says this will come into effect as from 26 December. CAPE TOWN - Golden Arrow Bus Services have announced a 4.45% fare hike, which will come into effect as from Monday, 26 December.The bus service and the Western Cape Transport Department makes provision for an annual adjustment to bus fares to cushion the effect of increases in operational expenses.The transport operator adds fuel and labour constitute about 72% of the total costs of conventional bus operations.Golden Arrow's Bronwen Dyke-Beyer says: Prices of items such as fuel, buses and digital operating systems are exposed to volatile exchange rate fluctuations and because the increase has also exceeded the average analysed consumer price index. The bus service currently accommodates about 220,000 passengers daily.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)